title: For Sale:  TAG Banshee Plate Carrier, Aires Armor Assault Pack/Full kit!
postcontent:
This is an excellent rig. It was put together for a deployment that never happened. As such, most of this gear is brand new. The plate carrier and the assault pack have seen light use during one field exercise but are in like new condition. Everything else (the pouches listed below) are brand new and have never seen the field. Below I have listed what is included in this auction, if it doesn't sell, I'll part it out and make more money next week. I just think it's a great set of kit and would like it to go to someone as is...

The Kit
- Tactical Assault Gear/Shellback Tactical Banshee Plate Carrier- Multicam (Retail $200)
- Tactical Assault Gear Banshee Cumberbund- Multicam (Retail $60)
- Ares Armor Combat XII Pack- Multicam (Retail $200)
- Tactical Assault Gear Utility Pouch- Multicam (Retail $25)
- HSGI Bleeder Blowout Medical pouch- Multicam (Retail $36)
- (3) Eagle Industries Double Mag pouch, 5.56 - Multicam (Retail $60)
- TOTAL RETAIL VALUE IS WELL OVER $500. THIS IS YOUR CHANCE TO GET THIS GEAR ON THE CHEAP! I'm selling this kit to fund a Remington 700 project, and for no other reason. 

First off, the Ares Armor Combat XII Pack. This thing is sweet. It has two internal hydration sleeves that also work well for organizing gear. It has pouches on top with room for (6) 30 round 5.56 magazines. These pouches have bungee retention. The pack can be used as a standalone assault pack or it can be integrated into your plate carrier (as I have done). The pack was originally designed for snipers and the way that the pockets are oriented on the back allows for an outstanding rifle rest. The entire pack is covered in MOLLE webbing that is multicam, and there is a large panel of multicam hook and loop on the outside of the mag pouches. This is the best thought out pack I've ever seen, hands down. 

I have this kit setup perfectly to integrate the Ares Armor Combat XII pack and the Banshee Plate Carrier. The clip system is show in the photographs. Basically, the shoulder straps of the pack are removed and the pack is clipped directly into your plate carrier. This removes the problem of numb arms, armpit chafing, and trying to slide the straps of your pack over your body armor. To access the pack, all you need to do is unclip one side of the pack and swing it over. Grab what you need and swing it back and re-clip. Too easy. You can reinstall the packs shoulder straps in 5 seconds by clipping them back in. 

I have the system to run the Banshee with or without the cumberbund. Both will be included in this auction. This is the most comfortable plate carrier system I have ever worn. Check out the reviews, you wont be disappointed. 

******All pouches are sold empty! I have them filled for display purposes only. BALLISTIC PLATES ARE NOT INCLUDED. The backpack will be empty and NO MAGAZINES ARE INCLUDED WITH THIS LISTING. THIS LISTING FOLLOWS COLORADO STATE LAWS AND POLICIES. No patches are included with this rig. *******

title: For Sale/Trade:  Have tools will travel! Rent a smith.
postcontent:
With tax time here ya'll are probably buying or building new toys, or getting some work done on old ones. With that comes many questions... Should I buy all the tools so I can build one rifle? Where on earth can I get some good help to build my dream AR? How do I make my DPMS into a solid shooter? 
The answer is you grab a Fox!
I am a small arms repairmen for the US Army. I have served in Afghanistan, and have over 3 years of experience working on Army weapon systems. While this is not a long time for a civilian gunsmith, this translates into working on thousands of weapon systems, and building hundreds of ARs. I am unwholesomely talented at my job. 
So what am I offering?
I have my own tools and gages. I will construct, upgrade, gage, and inspect your weaponry. Want to build an AR? Who better to do it than a government training mad-gun tech who has done this a thousand times in combat conditions. 

Rates are negotiable, and I will work for trade. Paying for my gas to come to you is a must. I will not travel more than 250 miles from post. I will not supply any parts because I still work for the army and this is a conflict of interest. What I will do is provide the very best of service and care for your weapon systems, build them safely and under the standards used by the US Military. If you are not satisfied by my level of work, I will fix it for free. 
Constructing weapon systems on your own is dangerous, and unforgiving potentially costing you hundreds of dollars in damaged parts. I will do it right the first time and make it last. I will also consult with you to get the very most performance for your dollar. I know every field mod that will build you the rifle or pistol that will performed under desired conditions. 

I look forward to hearing from you!

For almost a decade, Cold Steel® offered a small, wicked looking, boot knife called the Culloden®. It was based on the traditional Scottish "Black Knife" or "Skean Dhu", as it was more commonly referred to, in Gaelic, the ancient language of Scotland.

For the dawning years of this century, however, we have created an entirely new tactical folder, that takes some of its design cues from the ancient Skean Dhu. 

Our new Caledonian Edge™ features a number of modern variations and refinements on its older predecessor. The blade is made from virtually unbreakable San Mai III® blade construction and like the original Skean Dhu, features a thin, acutely pointed tip that's as sharp as the proverbial needle. It glides effortlessly through even the most puncture resistant materials. Additionally, its precisely and carefully hollow groud.

The traditional jimping seen on the Skean Dhu of old has been retained and provides an aggressive, non-slip platform for one's thumb and forefinger, allowing for better control when using the blade to cut or pierce.

The Caledonian Edge's™ handle sports a palm-hugging profile and a relatively thin cross section that augments its covert qualities. It's flat enough to resist rolling or twisting in one's palm yet comfortable enough to accommodate a wide range of gripping styles. A perfect blend of strength and beauty, it features a superstructure of attractive, highly polished, black Micarta scales and custom Titanium bolsters that are bolted, utilizing the latest in high-tech fasteners, to a strong, yet lightweight Titanium liner substructure.

The Caledonian Edge's™ leaf spring locking mechanism will protect your fingers from its sharp edge. It's made from Titanium and is hand fitted to the closest tolerances possible. It has proved incredibly tough and reliable even when exposed to our most brutal tests.

For discreet carry and immediate access, the Caledonian Edge™ comes with a brightly polished stainless steel pocket clip and thumb stud on the blade. This arrangement allows a wide variety of carry options as well as lightning quick one handed opening.

postcontent: Excellent condition, fairly low round count. If you read reviews, you will find that this is an EXTREMELY reliable .22lr that will shoot any ammo you give it. Unlike most "tactical" .22's, the upper is all metal (except for the handguard), the lower is a nice, thick polymer. The Sig 522 is also a great choice for a tactical .22 because it doesn't use expensive proprietary magazines. It uses AR15-22 conversion magazines such as the ones from Black Dog Machine (BDM). It comes with two 25-round and one 10-round BDM magazines. Well cleaned and oiled. Excellent cosmetically AND mechanically. The only issue 522's have ever had was a problem with the recoil rod using an e-clip where it attaches to the bolt. Sig offered a free upgrade that replaces the e-clip with a new drilled rod with a roll-pin tapped into it. This rifle HAS the new recoil assembly (even though I never had problems with the old one).  $525 for just the rifle, $600 with the 1400 rounds of ammo.

title: For Sale:  BULK .22LR AMMO!  Gun included (Smith & Wesson M&P 15-22 + extras)
postcontent:
The concept is simple. You buy this bag of ammo at an incredibly inflated price, and I'll throw in a gun to shoot it with.
And lots of magazines.
And a scope.
And a bipod.
And a foregrip.
And a buttpad.
And some more ammo.

Who wouldn't want a deal like this?
No, I won't sell the ammo without the gun. I would sell the gun without the ammo, but who in their right mind would want that?
No trades.

I DID NOT COUNT the ammo in this bag. It is a gallon-size ziploc bag, and it weighs 16.5 pounds. I DID measure out 1 lb, and counted that. It was 142 rounds. So 16.5 times that would be roughly 2,343 rounds. Plus or minus a few.

But wait, there's more! If you buy today, you also get the neato ammo can sitting next to the bag in the photo.


Here's some more information about the gun. What gun? The gun you're buying so you can get this ammo.
It's a Smith & Wesson M&P 15-22 A1 (model 811033).
It has a flash hider and removable iron sights, and comes with a bunch of extras (see below).

This is not one of the early models that had feed and ejection issues - it's a good one.
I've only had a few failures, and that was with the cheap Winchester XXX stuff, mainly due to the square nose jamming on the edge of the chamber.
This rifle will cycle subsonic 40gr rounds just fine with or without a suppressor attached, and the bulk pack Federal 32gr all day.

Extras Include:
NCStar BiPod
UTG Foldable foregrip
Barska 3x9x42IR scope
Adjustable iron sights
Two 50-round Black Dog drum magazines
Ten 25-round magazines
Three 10-round magazines
Butt pad
The ammo that is currently in the magazines (380 rounds)

If you pay my asking price, which I think is fair, I will include a UTG covert carry bag (see photo). If you offer me a low price, I'll start removing things like the bag, the ammo, the magazines, and the scope, which I will sell separately if needed. I'd prefer a package deal and a buyer with a fair attitude, but I will split it up if I have to.

I am not desperate for cash, so I will not let anyone "take it off my hands" for peanuts. The price is firm. Just try and beat it elsewhere. Make sure to include shipping, FFL, and sales tax in your calculations.

I'm looking for a no-hassle sale with a reasonable person who knows what he wants and doesn't screw around. If that's you, I'm willing to drive a bit to meet you halfway to make the deal.

For my own protection and peace of mind, I'll need you to have a CPL and WA driver's license. I will take a picture of these at the time of sale, but I won't send in any paperwork to the state. If that doesn't work for you, we can't make a deal.
